Theorem 1 (Existence and Construction of Brownian motion). There exists a probability space (Ω, Η, P) on which standard Brownian motion B exists and has continuous sample path.
Remarks: Recall that a Brownian motion is a process with the following properties:
(i) B(t) has stationary and independent increments;
(ii) B(t) is Gaussian with mean 0 and variance t;
(iii) B(t) is continuous in t.
